From: Vincenzo <vincenzo@vortex86-builder>
Date: Tue, 16 Jun 2026 15:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] tdb: replace 'typedef int bool' with '#include <stdbool.h>'

GCC 15+ defaults to -std=c23, where 'bool' is a keyword.
The 'typedef int bool;' in lib/ext2fs/tdb.c is illegal in C23
and causes a compilation error:

  error: 'bool' cannot be defined via 'typedef'
  note: 'bool' is a keyword with '-std=c23' onwards

Fix by including <stdbool.h> instead, which works in all C standards
(C99 through C23) and properly defines 'bool' as _Bool.

Signed-off-by: Vincenzo <vincenzo@vortex86-builder>

diff --git a/lib/ext2fs/tdb.c b/lib/ext2fs/tdb.c
index 188a9b8..d5b86d3 100644
--- a/lib/ext2fs/tdb.c
+++ b/lib/ext2fs/tdb.c
@@ -110,7 +110,7 @@
 #endif
 #endif
 
-typedef int bool;
+#include <stdbool.h>
 
 #include "tdb.h"
 
